When generate password button is clicked, alert stating "Let's generate a password"
User is prompted to enter a password length between 8 and 128 characters (must be a number)
Response is stored in a var
User is asked to confirm if they wish to include the following charater types:
    -lowercase
    -uppercase
    -numeric
    -special
Each response is stored in a var
Validate at least one character type is choosen
Password is generated and printed to the page




<button click>
alert(Let's generate a password)

var numChar = prompt(how long should your password be between 8 and 128 characters?)
    validate user entered a number (parseInt)
    if user entered a number between 8 and 128, continue
    else alert(you did not enter a number between 8 and 128. please try again) 

var optionsArray [includes the vars that have been selected by user]

var lowCase = confirm(should your password contain lowercase characters?)
    if answer = true include abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz added to possible options        
    if answer = false do not include

var upCase = confirm(should your password contain uppercase characters?)
    if answer = true include ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ as possible options
    if answer = false do not include

var numeric = confirm(should your password contain numeric characters?)
    if answer = true include 0123456789 as possible options
    if answer = false do not include

var special = confirm(should your password contain special characters?)
    if answer = true include !@#$%^&*()-_=+[{]}\|'";:/?.>,<] as possible options
    if answer = false do not include

if all vars = false (please try again)
             
generate numChar times the characters selected 
var password = ""
for (var i = 0; i < numChar; i++) {
   var index = math.floor(math.random) * optionsArray.length;
   
}


numChar times loop thru and select random char add into end of var password